3 years ago, I made a decision that changed my whole life. Its been 3 years since I moved from the sunny, warm tropics of the Philippines to the beautiful white, snowy Canada. The north western life is all new to me and Im loving it! And im proud to say that I have travelled and seen a lot of Canada. Im so fortunate and grateful for having a wonderful job that makes me see the the whole north. In 3 years Im so lucky to have ventured to 7 different provinces and 2 territories up north.

I once thought that life is dark and brutal but sometimes you gotta zigzag your way to the light and happiness. 

Thanks for the photo @thedana 🙏❤️

Would you believe me if I say this is in Quebec?

For those who don’t know, Îles de la Madeleine or Magdalen islands are a small archipelago located in the Gulf of St Lawrence. Although it is part of the province of Quebec, the islands are even closer to PEI and Newfoundland (literally in between these two provinces) than mainland Quebec. Hence the uniqueness of its landscapes and soil that is reddish in color. And do you know why the soil is red?

If you plan to visit the islands, check @ilesdelamadeleine and their website for more information. I highly recommend to add it in your list of places to travel in Canada. Super beautiful sceneries, warm and welcoming people, best sea food in the country! What more can you ask for?

Thanks @actioncanadafellowship for bringing me to this beautiful island!

The sun is beautiful but can also be deadly.

With the wildfire going on all throughout Canada and specially in Quebec happening right now, its a constant reminder of how climate change is getting serious. 

It’s heart breaking to see the news that due to the vastness of the fire, the authorities have difficulty containing it leading to thousands of people evacuated and hundreds losing their homes. 

And us in Outaouais now are experiencing the smog that is also detrimental to respiratory health. 

This is a reminder that we need to take global warming even more seriously and take necessary steps to fight it. Every action counts even how little it is.

#climatechange #globalwarming #wildfires #canadianwildlife #quebec #outaouais #takeaction #explorecanada #fightclimatechange #sunset #fire

What is the best feeling you’ve felt in your life?

I go first. It’s the feeling of being free. Free to do whatever you want to do. The feeling of being free to see, travel and enjoy the beauty of the world. Free to care. Free to love.

I’d say this experience is one of the best moments of my life. Im new to wildlife photography and its very addicting, capturing wildlife activity is not easy, it needs lots and lots of patience and dedication. High respect to the people who work with wildlife 🙏

And speaking of wildlife specialists, thanks to @matherpeter for spending time with me and sharing your beautiful experiences, and to @8ens for the warm welcome in Yukon and introducing me to Peter 😊

And lastly a big thank you to Public Policy Forum @actioncanadafellowship @scgemson , Anne and Safiya for giving me the opportunity to be a part of something big! To see Canada in a wider lens and to be able to share these beautiful experiences to other Canadians. ❤️

And of course barnarnar ❤️
